<TITLE> Sharma steers India to 195-5 against Sri Lanka </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 CANBERRA, Feb 12 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - Rohit Sharma smashed an unbeaten half-century to help India amass a daunting total of 195 for five from 29 overs in their rain-shortened tri-series one-day international against Sri Lanka at Manuka Oval on Tuesday. Sharma belted six boundaries and a six in a career-best 70 from just 64 balls as India's batsmen went on the rampage when the match finally got underway. Master batsman Sachin Tendulkar (32), captain Mahendra Singh Dhoni (31) and the in-form Gautam Gambhir (35) also scored at better than a run a ball in a frantic attempt to make up for lost time. Dhoni and Gambhir were both run out trying to keep the scoreboard ticking along while Lasith Malinga, Nuwan Kulasekera and Farveez Maharoof took one wicket apiece for Sri Lanka but spinner Muttiah Muralitharan missed out in his 300th one-day international. The start of the match was delayed for more than three and a half hours because of heavy morning showers and the prospect of a result was fading fast when rain returned at the end of India's innings. Australia's east coast has been drenched by torrential downpours in the past fortnight and the first two matches of the triangular series were washed out in Brisbane last week. Only two matches have produced results so far with Australia beating Sri Lanka by 128 runs in Sydney last Friday and India upsetting the Australians by five wickets in Melbourne two day's lat
